{"type":"message","id":"e7742b30","parentId":"5241a174","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:15:53.469Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xpi9jeuh4gq3_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 041507\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n- A key insight has emerged: Compression-Causal Duality - the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n- Next action is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe pending action says:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nI need to take ONE concrete action that advances this goal. The most logical first step would be to create a script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Implements the TIC classifier logic\r\n\r\nLet me look at what exists. The pulse logs are in `logs/pulse_*.md`. I should create a PowerShell script that implements the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nGiven the goals, I'll create a PowerShell script for the TIC classifier that:\r\n- Reads pulse logs\r\n- Extracts content\r\n- Attempts to classify invariants vs variants\r\n- Makes next-pulse predictions\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete file that advances this goal.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending actions more carefully:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nThe most concrete first step would be to create a TIC classifier script. Let me create `temporal_invariance_classifier.ps1`.\r\n\r\nI'll design a script that:\r\n1. Loads pulse logs\r\n2. Implements basic invariance detection (comparing consecutive pulses for recurring patterns)\r\n3. Uses pattern matching to predict next content\r\n\r\nThis advances toward the TIC experiment goal.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires a classifier that can identify invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs and predict next-pulse content. No such classifier exists yet in the codebase.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `temporal_invariance_classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that implements the TIC classifier, loads pulse logs, and measures invariant/variant classification accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Classifier (TIC)\r\n# Implements Compression-Causal Duality: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\r\n    [int]$MinPulseCount = 5,\r\n    [float]$Threshold = 0.7  # λ parameter\r\n)\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs sorted chronologically\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem \"$LogDir/pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt $MinPulseCount) {\r\n    Write-Host \"Insufficient pulse files. Found: $($pulseFiles.Count), Need: $MinPulseCount\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== Temporal Invariance Classifier ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Loaded: $($pulseFiles.Count) pulses\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Threshold (λ): $Threshold\"\r\n\r\n# Extract content from pulse logs\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    $pulses += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        File = $file.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Lines = ($content -split \"`n\").Count\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Build n-gram vocabulary (trigrams for initial implementation)\r\nfunction Get-NGrams {\r\n    param([string]$Text, [int]$N = 3)\r\n    $words = ($Text -split '\\W+' | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 2 })\r\n    $ngrams = @()\r\n    for ($i = 0; $i -le $words.Count - $N; $i++) {\r\n        $ngrams += ($words[$i..($i+$N-1)] -join ' ')\r\n    }\r\n    return $ngrams\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate invariance score between two pulses\r\nfunction Get-InvarianceScore {\r\n    param([string]$Pulse1, [string]$Pulse2)\r\n    $ngrams1 = Get-NGrams $Pulse1\r\n    $ngrams2 = Get-NGrams $Pulse2\r\n    $intersection = ($ngrams1 | Where-Object { $ngrams2 -contains $_ }).Count\r\n    $union = (($ngrams1 + $ngrams2) | Select-Object -Unique).Count\r\n    if ($union -eq 0) { return 0 }\r\n    return $intersection / $union\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify pulses as invariant or variant relative to previous\r\n$classifications = @()\r\nfor ($i = 1; $i -lt $pulses.Count; $i++) {\r\n    $score = Get-InvarianceScore $pulses[$i-1].Content $pulses[$i].Content\r\n    $isInvariant = $score -ge $Threshold\r\n    $classifications += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        From = $pulses[$i-1].File\r\n        To = $pulses[$i].File\r\n        Score = [math]::Round($score, 3)\r\n        Classification = if ($isInvariant) { \"INVARIANT\" } else { \"VARIANT\" }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Output classification results\r\nWrite-Host \"`n=== Classification Results ===\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\n$invariantCount = ($classifications | Where-Object { $_.Classification -eq \"INVARIANT\" }).Count\r\n$variantCount = ($classifications | Where-Object { $_.Classification -eq\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:15:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774340153469}}
